narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Your advisor determines the success and enjoyability of your project much more than the content of the project itself. Don't choose an advisor that you hate, but also don't choose one that will let you slack.
If you're engineering, you have to do it. Get started early, and do it with a professor that you like.
It's the Mechanical Engineering Senior Project. It is what you want to make of it. Make sure you work with a good advisor and you'll be all set.
I would recommend it. You make what you want the class to be.
It is what you make it. Make sure to pick an adviser who will be engaged with you during the whole semester.
